\cb5 If the process of modifying to restrict refutation continues long enough, the ultimate result is the type of hypothesis that Popper sardonically calls \'93irrefutable.\'94 This may sound good, but think about what it means. It is a hypothesis that cannot possibly be proven false\'97one so wishy-washy that no possible observation is incompatible with it. That kind of hypothesis doesn\'92t really say anything.\cb1 \
\
\cb5 The basics of confirmation in place, let\'92s return to Hempel\'92s paradox with this added perspective. The first thing that concerns most people hearing the paradox for the first time is this business about the contrapositive. \'93Nonblack things\'94 and \'93nonravens\'94 are awkward constructions. Is \'93All nonblack things are nonravens\'94 really equivalent to \'93All ravens are black\'94? If it\'92s not, there is no paradox.\cb1 \
\
\cb5 It may come as a surprise that observations of black ravens are virtually irrelevant to the ultimate truth or falsity of \'93All ravens are black.\'94\cb1 \
